{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CaQZ7wyi1XFD1ubF8rb8YF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that ES is only writing GC logs, not the standard application logs. This is because by default in ES 8.x, logs go to stdout (JSON). But Filebeat needs to collect something. Let me check what logs might be available.\n\nActually, for ES 8.x, the default logging goes to stdout in JSON format, which means I can have Filebeat collect from the stdout/stderr of the container. But there's no shared log volume.\n\nOne approach:\n1. For Metricbeat: sidecar that connects to the local ES node via HTTPS and collects metrics\n2. For Filebeat: I could either add a shared emptyDir volume and configure ES to write logs there, or use Filebeat's Kubernetes autodiscover to read directly from the pod's stdout/stderr.\n\nFor the sidecar approach with stack monitoring, Metricbeat would hit the local ES API endpoint while Filebeat reads from ES logs on a shared volume. ES 8.x uses log4j2 by default and writes to both console and files, so I need to verify the current logging configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1209,"cache_read_input_tokens":36965,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1209},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d41423-0c6e-42cb-88b0-c36637753ff9","uuid":"592b86ff-c181-4ab9-a9ca-183b38f09af1","request_id":"req_011CcMg9S1htEsLaURXY2nw5"}
