itoring cluster has different compatibility rules.\n\nLooking at the compatibility matrix, Beats 8.x can output to ES 7.x (one major version back), but there's a potential mismatch with monitoring index templates—Metricbeat 8.x would try to write to `.monitoring-es-8-*` indices that expect ES 8.x templates, which a 7.17.9 cluster wouldn't have. I need to think through whether the 7.x monitoring cluster can actually accept and handle those newer index formats.\n\nActually, the real issue is that Kibana 7.x looks for `.monitoring-es-7-*` indices for its stack monitoring UI, so I should use Metricbeat 7.17.9 instead. The key REST APIs it relies on—like `GET /_nodes/stats`, `GET /_cluster/stats`, and `GET /_stats`—are all stable and available in both 7.x and 8.x, so Metricbeat 7.17.9 should work fine collecting from ES 8.x. I'll go with Metricbeat 7.17.9 and Filebeat 7.17.9 since both images are already available, then I need to check the monitoring cluster's current state to see what indices already exist.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5359,"cache_read_input_tokens":43682,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5359},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d41423-0c6e-42cb-88b0-c36637753ff9","uuid":"6f92b987-7bde-4324-8326-c18e813202cd","request_id":"req_011CcMgHdw2fBnvHmAqC3aY3"}
