{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JU8juGgDmNZqJKMt1hSEJX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The monitoring cluster has no monitoring indices yet. Now I have a clear plan. Let me create all the necessary resources.\n\nPlan:\n1. Create ConfigMap `es-log4j2-config` - log4j2.properties with RollingFile appenders\n2. Create ConfigMap `metricbeat-config` - metricbeat.yml\n3. Create ConfigMap `filebeat-config` - filebeat.yml\n4. Patch StatefulSet `es-cluster` - add sidecars and volumes\n5. Patch StatefulSet `es-data-new` - add sidecars and volumes\nI'll start by writing out the YAML configurations. For log4j2.properties, I'm keeping the existing console appenders for deprecation, slowlogs, and audit, but adding a RollingFile appender for the main server log. For Metricbeat, I need to enable xpack to use the proper monitoring index format and collect the monitoring data.\n\nFor the Filebeat configuration, I'll use the elasticsearch module with server logs enabled. Now for the StatefulSet patches, I need to add the same sidecar containers and volumes to both `es-cluster` and `es-data-new`. The key additions are the emptyDir for logs and configmaps for metricbeat, filebeat, and the log4j2 config. For the Elasticsearch container itself, I need to mount the logs directory and override the existing log4j2.properties file using a configmap subPath mount.\n\nRegarding the log4j2.properties, I realize that subPath mounts won't auto-update when the configmap changes, but that's acceptable for this use case. The existing config already has a RateLimitingFilter reference for the deprecation logger that I need to preserve. My approach is to take the full existing log4j2.properties and add a RollingFile appender for server logs alongside the existing console appender.\n\nI'll keep the current `rolling` appender as Console for stdout logging, add a new `rolling_file` appender as RollingFile for Filebeat to consume, and add `rolling_file` to the rootLogger. This maintains backward compatibility while enabling file-based log collection.\n\nFor Metricbeat, I need to configure the elasticsearch module with key metricsets like node_stats, index_summary, shards, cluster_stats, ml_job, ccr, and enrich. With xpack monitoring enabled, these will be sent as monitoring documents to the `.monitoring-es-7-*` indices. Now I'll write out all the manifests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3107,"cache_read_input_tokens":49041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3107},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d41423-0c6e-42cb-88b0-c36637753ff9","uuid":"5be89549-49d1-4cd1-b8ea-a8082f252bac","request_id":"req_011CcMgM7VK9ANsNNncGeo5e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JU8juGgDmNZqJKMt1hSEJX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything I need. The plan is:\n1. Add a `log4j2.properties` ConfigMap that writes ES server logs to a shared volume\n2. Add Metricbeat and Filebeat ConfigMaps\n3. Patch both StatefulSets to add the sidecars + shared log volume\n\nLet me create all manifests:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3107,"cache_read_input_tokens":49041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3107},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d41423-0c6e-42cb-88b0-c36637753ff9","uuid":"06f79dc0-c1bd-4c20-9636-7aba805af3fb","request_id":"req_011CcMgM7VK9ANsNNncGeo5e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JU8juGgDmNZqJKMt1hSEJX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Xnw9KvRdtD2Gf7nA8Sm4LQ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/monitoring-setup.yaml","content":"---\n# Override log4j2 to write server logs to a file (shared with Filebeat sidecar)\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-log4j2-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  log4j2.properties: |\n    status = error\n\n    ######## Server JSON - Console ############################\n    appender.rolling.type = Console\n    appender.rolling.name = rolling\n    appender.rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.server\n\n    ######## Server JSON - File (for Filebeat sidecar) ########\n    appender.rolling_file.type = RollingFile\n    appender.rolling_file.name = rolling_file\n    appender.rolling_file.fileName = /usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/elasticsearch-server.json\n    appender.rolling_file.filePattern = /usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/elasticsearch-server-%i.json.gz\n    appender.rolling_file.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.rolling_file.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.server\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.type = Policies\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.size.type = SizeBasedTriggeringPolicy\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.size.size = 64MB\n    appender.rolling_file.strategy.type = DefaultRolloverStrategy\n    appender.rolling_file.strategy.max = 2\n\n    rootLogger.level = info\n    rootLogger.appenderRef.rolling.ref = rolling\n    rootLogger.appenderRef.rolling_file.ref = rolling_file\n\n    ######## Deprecation JSON #######################\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.name = deprecation_rolling\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.layout.dataset = deprecation.elasticsearch\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.filter.rate_limit.type = RateLimitingFilter\n\n    appender.header_warning.type = HeaderWarningAppender\n    appender.header_warning.name = header_warning\n\n    logger.deprecation.name = org.elasticsearch.deprecation\n    logger.deprecation.level = WARN\n    logger.deprecation.appenderRef.deprecation_rolling.ref = deprecation_rolling\n    logger.deprecation.appenderRef.header_warning.ref = header_warning\n    logger.deprecation.additivity = false\n\n    ######## Search slowlog JSON ####################\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.name = index_search_slowlog_rolling\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.index_search_slowlog\n\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.name = index.search.slowlog\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.level = trace\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.appenderRef.index_search_slowlog_rolling.ref = index_search_slowlog_rolling\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.additivity = false\n\n    ######## Indexing slowlog JSON ##################\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.name = index_indexing_slowlog_rolling\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.index_indexing_slowlog\n\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.name = index.indexing.slowlog.index\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.level = trace\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.appenderRef.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.ref = index_indexing_slowlog_rolling\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.additivity = false\n\n    logger.org_apache_pdfbox.name = org.apache.pdfbox\n    logger.org_apache_pdfbox.level = off\n\n    logger.org_apache_poi.name = org.apache.poi\n    logger.org_apache_poi.level = off\n\n    logger.org_apache_fontbox.name = org.apache.fontbox\n    logger.org_apache_fontbox.level = off\n\n    logger.org_apache_xmlbeans.name = org.apache.xmlbeans\n    logger.org_apache_xmlbeans.level = off\n\n    logger.com_amazonaws.name = com.amazonaws\n    logger.com_amazonaws.level = warn\n\n    logger.com_amazonaws_jmx_SdkMBeanRegistrySupport.name = com.amazonaws.jmx.SdkMBeanRegistrySupport\n    logger.com_amazonaws_jmx_SdkMBeanRegistrySupport.level = error\n\n    logger.com_amazonaws_metrics_AwsSdkMetrics.name = com.amazonaws.metrics.AwsSdkMetrics\n    logger.com_amazonaws_metrics_AwsSdkMetrics.level = error\n\n    logger.com_amazonaws_auth_profile_internal_BasicProfileConfigFileLoader.name = com.amazonaws.auth.profile.internal.BasicProfileConfigFileLoader\n    logger.com_amazonaws_auth_profile_internal_BasicProfileConfigFileLoader.level = error\n\n    logger.com_amazonaws_services_s3_internal_UseArnRegionResolver.name = com.amazonaws.services.s3.internal.UseArnRegionResolver\n    logger.com_amazonaws_services_s3_internal_UseArnRegionResolver.level = error\n\n    appender.audit_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.audit_rolling.name = audit_rolling\n    appender.audit_rolling.layout.type = PatternLayout\n    appender.audit_rolling.layout.pattern = {\\\n                    \"type\":\"audit\", \\\n                    \"timestamp\":\"%d{yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss,SSSZ}\"\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"node.name\":\"%enc{%map{node.name}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"event.type\":\"%enc{%map{event.type}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"event.action\":\"%enc{%map{event.action}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"user.name\":\"%enc{%map{user.name}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"url.path\":\"%enc{%map{url.path}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    %varsNotEmpty{, \"request.method\":\"%enc{%map{request.method}}{JSON}\"}\\\n                    }%n\n\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.name = org.elasticsearch.xpack.security.audit.logfile.LoggingAuditTrail\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.level = info\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.appenderRef.audit_rolling.ref = audit_rolling\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.additivity = false\n\n    logger.xmlsig.name = org.apache.xml.security.signature.XMLSignature\n    logger.xmlsig.level = error\n    logger.samlxml_decrypt.name = org.opensaml.xmlsec.encryption.support.Decrypter\n    logger.samlxml_decrypt.level = fatal\n    logger.saml2_decrypt.name = org.opensaml.saml.saml2.encryption.Decrypter\n    logger.saml2_decrypt.level = fatal\n\n---\n# Metricbeat config: collect metrics from local ES node, ship to monitoring cluster\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: metricbeat-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  metricbeat.yml: |\n    metricbeat.modules:\n    - module: elasticsearch\n      metricsets:\n        - node\n        - node_stats\n        - index\n        - index_recovery\n        - index_summary\n        - shard\n        - ml_job\n        - pending_tasks\n      period: 10s\n      hosts: [\"https://localhost:9200\"]\n      username: \"elastic\"\n      password: \"${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\"\n      ssl.certificate_authorities:\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n      ssl.verification_mode: \"certificate\"\n      xpack.enabled: true\n\n    output.elasticsearch:\n      hosts: [\"http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200\"]\n\n    setup.ilm.enabled: false\n\n---\n# Filebeat config: collect ES server logs from shared volume, ship to monitoring cluster\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: filebeat-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  filebeat.yml: |\n    filebeat.modules:\n    - module: elasticsearch\n      server:\n        enabled: true\n        var.paths:\n          - \"/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/elasticsearch-server.json\"\n      gc:\n        enabled: false\n      audit:\n        enabled: false\n      slowlog:\n        enabled: false\n\n    output.elasticsearch:\n      hosts: [\"http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200\"]\n\n    setup.ilm.enabled: false\n    setup.template.settings:\n      index.number_of_shards: 1\n      index.number_of_replicas: 0\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3107,"cache_read_input_tokens":49041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3107},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1d41423-0c6e-42cb-88b0-c36637753ff9","uuid":"b2b4c734-23e3-4590-b1c4-4293c19b70d1","request_id":"req_011CcMgM7VK9ANsNNncGeo5e"}
