{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UfAS1g5VBzxVnbQc56VZhn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `ConfigMap/es-log4j2-config` — adds a `RollingFile` appender to ES's log4j2 alongside the existing console appender, writing server logs to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/elasticsearch-server.json`\n- `ConfigMap/metricbeat-config` — Metricbeat 7.17.9 config: elasticsearch module (xpack mode, HTTPS+TLS to `localhost:9200`) → outputs to monitoring cluster\n- `ConfigMap/filebeat-config` — Filebeat 7.17.9 config: plain JSON log input reading from the shared log file → outputs to monitoring cluster\n\n**Both StatefulSets patched** (`es-cluster` 3-node + `es-data-new` 2-node):\n- Added `es-logs` emptyDir shared between ES and Filebeat containers\n- ES container: mounts `es-logs` at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs` and the custom log4j2 config\n- `metricbeat` sidecar: collects metrics via HTTPS using the `elastic` credential + CA cert, ships in xpack monitoring format\n- `filebeat` sidecar: tails the shared log file, ships parsed JSON logs\n\n**Monitoring cluster now has:**\n- `.monitoring-es-7-mb-2026.06.24` — 918+ docs (metrics path via Metricbeat)\n- `filebeat-7.17.9-2026.06.24` — 862+ docs (logs path via Filebeat)\n\n**Note on the Filebeat module:** The built-in `elasticsearch` module pipeline drops all ES 8.x logs (it checks for `type: server` which ES 8.x ECS format omits). A plain `filebeat.inputs` log input with `json.keys_under_root` bypasses this and correctly ships the ES 8.x ECS-formatted logs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":981,"cache_read_input_tokens":101928,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":981},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":nu